															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordstonefish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2527320); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2527320&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203757" alt="LordStonefish" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2527320)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lordstonefish" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2527320); return false;" >LordStonefish</a></span> <span class="odate time_1472674002 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">31 Aug 2016 20:06</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2581873">
									

<p>For the record, this is neither about Montauk nor 682. It uses them as literary device, but it's not about them. Nor is it a manner of guess the skip. This is its own thing.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;As&nbsp;many&nbsp;don't&nbsp;understand,&nbsp;here's&nbsp;the&nbsp;explanation</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;SPOLIERS</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Nominally this poem is related to <a href="/scp-2747">SCP-2747</a>, but moreso it's an angry, surrealist abstraction of the SCP format. The object is a collection of dumb horror cliches, the subtextual emotion is at the forefront, the interview is nothing but quotes from other interviews, and the containment procedures no longer exist.</p>
<p>This shows the degrading of the Foundation as a narrative and as a concept. The anafabula was generated by imagery and iconography from all the skips mentioned as they are stories within our fictional universe. As the anafabula begins to eat the narrative of the Foundation, this is what will happen. Things start to blur and become unsure. We have no way of telling if this is a new SCP or one we've read before. Concepts start to repeat. Sentences become meaningless. Before the stanzas disappear entirely we are left desperately clinging to our concepts, but before we realize it, our stories are eaten and we fall into the void.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

							</div>

								
