					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/scorpion451" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1918720); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1918720&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203757" alt="Scorpion451" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1918720)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/scorpion451" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1918720); return false;" >Scorpion451</a></span> <span class="odate time_1472746945 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Sep 2016 16:22</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2583263">
									

<p>Interesting&#8230;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;My&nbsp;own&nbsp;'what&nbsp;I&nbsp;took&nbsp;from&nbsp;it'&nbsp;interpretation</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Like&nbsp;I&nbsp;said&nbsp;above,&nbsp;'How&nbsp;many&nbsp;holes&nbsp;before&nbsp;it&nbsp;all&nbsp;unravels?':</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I read it as an O5 reminiscing on their career&#8230; what they remember of it, that is.</p>
<p>Amnestics are a fix-all to the Foundation. Exposed to a cogitohazard? Amnestics. Survive a 682 breach too traumatized to function? Amnestics. Reality warper goes berserk in Manhattan? Amestics for everyone. If no one remembers a thing, and you destroy the evidence, it never happened. Cut out the flaw in reality, patch over the hole, good as new&#8230; so long as no one looks at the seam too closely. How many holes can you cut and patch in reality before it all unravels?</p>
<p>Digging deeper, they use amnestics on themselves as often as on civilians. How much time does a typical Foundation employee loose over their career? How much trauma and guilt do they expunge from their own minds? How much do they choose to unsee? How many names do they choose to unlearn? How many holes can you cut in your own mind before it all unravels?</p>
<p>And for the O5&#8230;the guilt of decisions made for the greater good, the terror of seeing the world unfiltered by the lies you tell others so they can sleep, the burden of knowing that the end of the world is always just one mistake away (and that that mistake could be yours)&#8230; and the one great temptation of knowing there is a simple method to just make it all&#8230;go away. How many holes in your soul&#8230;?</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

